obo:ECO_0001230  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4491  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: This annotation is part of a systematic annotation of all synaptic vesicle V-ATPases.\n\nRationale: The luminal V-ATPase is known to be present in the membrane of synaptic vesicles where it drives the import of neurotransmitter molecules via a range of antiporter protein complexes (PMID:28383767). The mammalian V-ATPases consists of a peripheral V1 domain and an integral V0 domain (PMID: 16524922). Two-step differential centrifugation and a high-affinity effector protein SidK was used to purify mammalian V-ATPase subunit homologs from synaptic vesicles of rat brain. SDS-PAGE was used to isolate V-ATPase subunits (Fig1B and S1A) and was subjected to mass spectrometry for subunit identification (Fig1C and S1B). Cryogenic Electron Microscopy was used to yield 3D atomic maps of the V-ATPase V1 (Fig 1D, 2A, S5 and S7) and V0 subunits (Fig3A) and demonstrates that ATP6V1A is part of the V1 domain of mammalian V-ATPase.\n\n- Based on the constructed 3D cryogenic electron microscopic model , the \"extrinsic component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Membranes enriched for synaptic vesicles were collected from adult Norwegian rat brains. SidK1-278-3xFLAG solution applied to agarose beads and centrifuged. The flow through was then subjected to SDS-PAGE, mass spectropmetry and cryoEM." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" ;
        dc:date           "2020-12-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4491" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

